          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "4PI1A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " At near threshold energies the reaction is",
                "reported to be isotropic in the center-of-mass frame.",
                "Therefore, the total cross section can be expressed",
                "as 4*Pi times the zero degree center-of-mass cross",
                "section (see Eq. 4 of Reference). The difficulty",
                "arises from the fact that near the threshold energy",
                "two neutron energies can be assigned to one proton",
                "energy, which is reflected in the yield factor (see",
                "Eq. 5 of Ref.). However, using only the low-energy",
                "tail of the yield function with the measured neutron",
                "spectra the shape of the (p,n) cross section curve",
                "can be determined. Proton energies were calculated",
                "from neutron energies using the reaction kinematics."
              ]
            }
          ],
